In your second example, the type of the map is `std::map<int, std::string>` and the type of the second parameter `"apple"` is a `const char[5]`, which cannot be deduced to be a `std::string` or an `int` implicitly. Therefore, the compiler cannot deduce the types used by the map and fails to compile.

